Wife and I came here around noon today (Tuesday Feb. 16 in the eternal year of our Covid  2021). Parking was easy as they have a large parking lot attached to the restaurant with at least 20 spaces. Only a few customers inside so we put our anti-covid-superpandemic-eradicater masks on and went straight up to the counter to order. Menu is typical BBQ joint, with full menu of goodies - pulled pork, brisket, chopped chicken, cole slaw, baked beans, etc.  My wife ordered the spare rib plate with green beans and Brunswick stew, also comes with cornbread. Ribs were a little dry but tasty - they come without sauce, you add the sauce, the stew was excellent and the green beans are the flat kind, but had a nice smoky flavor to them, a little underseasoned but still good. Cornbread was sweet, and moist not dry (I had to use the word MOIST - say it with me..."moist"...see don't you feel better after saying MOIST more than once today? You're welcome).  I had the chopped chicken plate with potato salad and coleslaw as my sides. Chopped chicken was a little underflavored and not enough sauce, so I added some of their sweet sauce later, so that turned out better. I like coleslaw on my BBQ samminch - yes I said samminch. SLAWBQ! The slaw was pretty good, a little more mayo and couple degrees colder would have been perfect but it was good. The only thing I didn't enjoy at first was the potato salad - I guess pandemics make people stop putting mustard in potato salad. I'm pretty picky about my tater-salad, and this was a letdown as it was probably made with mayo/sourcream/dill...not very southern (where's the MUSTARD?) so what I did was I went over to the sauce counter and got some of their "Carolina mustard" BBQ sauce and put that in the potato salad and Bingo it was better.  For my drink I had the unsweet tea with lemonade because yeah, tea and BBQ. They do have beer by the bottle but I was driving and didn't want to get a DUI and miss any of the wonderful goings-on in the world right now (lawdy I might have missed something as spectacular as that last superbowl halftime show)!  So if you are: 1. Looking for decent BBQ close to downtown 2. A BBQ place to "dine in" 3. A place to park at a BBQ joint without paying $20 to park 4. A no frills place where you won't get the evil-eye for eating without a mask on (yes masks are required to enter but you can take them off to eat, instead of eating by osmosis like many places expect you to lately) 5. Plenty of elbow room in the dining area 6. Good basic counter-service and fast food service  ...then this is your joint. Definitely recommend and will be back, with mustard in hand.

Ordered online for pick-up, told me it would be ready in half an hour, so I got there 30 minutes later. There was no dedicated order pick-up area and they told me to stand in line with everyone else. After standing in line for 15 minutes they told me my food wasn’t ready yet and said it should come out soon without asking/checking with the kitchen. Waited another 15 minutes at which point I voiced my displeasure and they finally checked in the kitchen. Turns out the food was ready and sitting there waiting for who knows how long. So by the time I got home the food was cold. Because all in all it took almost 1.5h before I could finally eat (between the wait time and the drive back) I didn’t bother putting everything in the microwave or oven, but honestly speaking I don’t think heating the food up would have made it much better. The ribs were dry, the brisket was dry and had a weird color, and the chicken wings had a sweet sauce that just wasn’t it (and the chicken itself wasn’t great either). The only thing that was kind of good was the pulled pork, but it was mostly because of the sauce. Green beans were bad, Mac and cheese was bland, and the fries were undercooked and had a pathetic attempt to some sort of seasoning on them. Anyways, decide for yourself if you want to go here or not. Judging from some of the other reviews here there are a lot people that enjoyed the food here. Maybe the restaurant just had a bad day; it did seem they were understaffed. I, however, am not inclined to give them another chance.
